title.narrative: ESSENTIAL NUTRITION SERVICES

description.narrative: Nutrition systems and provisions strengthened to deliver essential nutrition services package including nutrition in emergency to the targeted children, pregnant women and lactating mother., which contributes to Child Health, Community-Based Management Of Acute Malnutrition, Infant And Young Child Feeding, Micronutrients, Nutrition And Emergencies, Operations Support To Programme Delivery, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Evaluations, Research And Data, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The most vulnerable children and women access a minimum social protection package
